requirement is <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">zero</NUMEX>." <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">April Testimony</TIMEX> at <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">41</NUMEX> (testimony of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Jack</ENAMEX>
Londen, <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">Attorney</ENAMEX> at <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Law</ENAMEX>).
The legislative history contains no evidence that <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Congress</ENAMEX>
intended LSC representation of legal permanent <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">residents</ENAMEX> and other
<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">aliens</ENAMEX> to turn on the accident of where an alien happened to be at
the moment the cause of action arose or the litigation commenced,
or to require the alien to be continuously physically present
