believe that <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Congress</ENAMEX> intended to force <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">resident aliens</ENAMEX> to choose
between temporary trips outside the <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">United States</ENAMEX> and continued
representation in pending litigation. The <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Commission</ENAMEX> has not been
able to discern any congressional purpose that would be served by
tying the right to representation on movements that have no effect
on either the alien's lawful immigration status or her legal right
to pursue her claim in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">U.S.</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">courts</ENAMEX>. The <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Commission</ENAMEX> is unwilling to
recommend an interpretation of the statute that produces such
